<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,930,1353]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,1002,1028]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Biology</emphasis>
. Reared from asexual galls of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fitch, 1859)" authorityName="Gillette" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Fitch" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[644,1138,1002,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Disholcaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercusglobulus">
<emphasis box="[644,981,1003,1029]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Disholcaspis quercusglobulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fitch, A. M. D." box="[998,1130,1002,1029]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="781 - 829" refId="ref102802" refString="Fitch, A. M. D. (1859) Fifth report on the noxious and other insects of the state of New York. Insects infesting deciduous forest trees. Annual Reports of the New York State Agricultural Society, 18, 781 - 829." type="journal article" year="1859">Fitch, 1859</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
on a white oak, and from similar galls described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[449,687,1039,1066]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="47 - 72" refId="ref105046" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von (1861) On the Cynipidae of the North American oaks and their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 1 (3), 47 - 72." type="journal article" year="1861">Osten-Sacken (1861)</bibRefCitation>
on an unknown oak (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[934,1158,1038,1065]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="331 - 380" refId="ref105131" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von (1865) Contributions to the natural history of the Cynipidae of the United States and of their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 4 (3), 331 - 380." type="journal article" year="1865">Osten-Sacken 1865</bibRefCitation>
), which may correspond to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walsh, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Walsh" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[180,672,1075,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Disholcaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercusmamma">
<emphasis box="[180,507,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Disholcaspis quercusmamma</emphasis>
(Walsh, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Bassett, 1890" authorityName="Bassett" authorityYear="1890" box="[710,1093,1075,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holcaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duricoria">
<emphasis box="[710,935,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Holcaspis duricoria</emphasis>
Bassett, 1890
</taxonomicName>
) on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gillette 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Gillette" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1142,1432,1075,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Synergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[1142,1257,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. bicolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gillette, C. P." box="[1273,1424,1075,1102]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="85 - 100" refId="ref102997" refString="Gillette, C. P. (1896) A monograph of the genus Synergus. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 23, 85 - 100." type="journal article" year="1896">Gillette 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Also, from galls of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walsh" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[377,590,1111,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Disholcaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercusmamma">
<emphasis box="[377,590,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">D. quercusmamma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[648,780,1111,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Trigonaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[648,780,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Trigonaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis box="[802,1002,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">quercusforticorne</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walsh, B. D." box="[1020,1162,1111,1138]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="443 - 500" refId="ref108576" refString="Walsh, B. D. (1864) On dimorphism in the hymenopterous genus Cynips; with an appendix, containing hints for a new classification of Cynipidae and a list of Cynipidae, including descriptions of several new species, inhabiting the oak-galls of Illinois. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 2, 443 - 500." type="journal article" year="1864">Walsh, 1864</bibRefCitation>
) (= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walsh, 1864)) (Gillette 1896)" authorityName=") (Gillette" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Walsh" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Biorhiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forticornis">
<emphasis box="[1213,1436,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Biorhiza forticornis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walsh, B. D." box="[161,301,1147,1174]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="443 - 500" refId="ref108576" refString="Walsh, B. D. (1864) On dimorphism in the hymenopterous genus Cynips; with an appendix, containing hints for a new classification of Cynipidae and a list of Cynipidae, including descriptions of several new species, inhabiting the oak-galls of Illinois. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 2, 443 - 500." type="journal article" year="1864">Walsh, 1864</bibRefCitation>
)) (
<bibRefCitation author="Gillette, C. P." box="[335,486,1147,1174]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="85 - 100" refId="ref102997" refString="Gillette, C. P. (1896) A monograph of the genus Synergus. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 23, 85 - 100." type="journal article" year="1896">Gillette 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the latter considered incertae sedis after 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Ferrer-Suay, M. &amp; Cuesta-Porta, V. &amp; Lobato-Vila, I." box="[956,1253,1147,1173]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="110" refId="ref106558" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Ferrer-Suay, M., Cuesta-Porta, V. &amp; Lobato-Vila, I. (2018) Does Biorhiza Westwood, 1840 (Hym.: Cynipidae) exist in Mexico? Folia Entomologica Mexicana, Nueva Serie, 4 (3), 110 â€¾ 127." type="journal article" year="2018">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[1112,1168,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,930,1353]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1183,1209]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[373,421,1183,1209]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osten-Sacken" authorityYear="1865" box="[558,791,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Synergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campanula">
<emphasis box="[558,791,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Synergus campanula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was examined and the species was redescribed and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Equihua-Martinez, A. &amp; Estrada-Venegas, E. &amp; Cibrian-Tovar, D. &amp; Barrera-Ruiz, U. M. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[257,594,1219,1245]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref103815" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Equihua-Martinez, A., Estrada-Venegas, E., Cibrian-Tovar, D., Barrera-Ruiz, U. M. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2020 c) Synergus Hartig species group (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) with partially smooth mesopleurae from the New World. Zootaxa, 4822 (1), 1 - 38. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4822.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[399,448,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. (2020c: 11)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,930,1353]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
The host plant is not mentioned in the original description, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gillette" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Fitch" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[915,1134,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Disholcaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercusglobulus">
<emphasis box="[915,1134,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">D. quercusglobulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burks 1979:" baseAuthorityYear="1078" box="[1303,1388,1255,1281]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[1303,1388,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Burks 1979: 1092)" baseAuthorityName="Burks 1979:" baseAuthorityPageNumber="1092" baseAuthorityYear="1092" box="[151,522,1291,1317]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prinoides">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. prinoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Burks, B. D." box="[306,513,1291,1317]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref102011" refString="Burks, B. D. (1979) Superfamily Cynipoidea. In: Krombein, K. V., Hurd, P. D., Smith, D. R. &amp; Burks, B. D. (Eds.), Catalog of Hymenoptera in America north of Mexico. Vol. 1. Symphyta and Apocrita (Parasitica). Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington D. C., pp. 1045 - 1107" type="book" year="1979">Burks 1979: 1092</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Also, recorded from 
<taxonomicName box="[766,872,1291,1317]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prinus">
<emphasis box="[766,872,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. prinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this name applies to two different species: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muehlenbergii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. muehlenbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[366,499,1327,1353]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[366,499,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Q. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
